January Home Sales Reach Highest Level in a Decade, Realtors Say Supply of existing homes remains historically low By @EricMorath Feb. 22, 2017 10:27 a.m. ET 
U.S. home sales rose in January to the highest level since February 2007, a sign last yearâ€™s momentum in the sector extended into 2017 despite a limited supply of properties and rising prices. 
Purchases of previously owned homes, which account for the vast majority of U.S. sales, increased 3.3% in January from December to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 5.69 million, the National Association of Realtors said Wednesday....
